cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the application of deep learning models for the detection of melanoma and skin lesion cancers using dermoscopic images. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) which are commonly used in image recognition tasks and fall under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging which can be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM).
